hopobject.body: Until August alternativemed.biz It was revealed this week that in the four months leading up to the 2012 Olympics, Jadco, the Jamaican anti-doping body, conducted one out-of-competition test, 11 in the seven months before the Games. Out of competition is when dopers dope. Jamaica has a reputation for producing sprinters but it is now acquiring one for producing sprinters who dope. Asafa Powell â once the fastest man in the world â three-times Olympic gold-medal winner Veronica Campbell-Brown and Sherone Simpson, another Olympic gold winner, are among a number to test positive.
